OL,3,C'Entirely unacceptable': Public urged
OL,4,Cto report hate crimes
OL,6,F"We also work closely with a range of
OL,7,Fcommunity and voluntary groups,
OL,8,Fstatutory partners, and advocacy
OL,9,Forganisations to ensure victims are
OL,10,Fsupported and their voices heard.
OL,12,F"If someone feels unable to report
OL,13,Fdirectly to police, then the Hate
OL,14,FCrime Advocacy Service (HCAS) can
OL,15,Fprovide independent, confidential
OL,16,Fassistance to help you navigate your
OL,17,Foptions.
